OL,6,F"I have always held the view that, for
OL,7,Fthis reason, the state should serve a
OL,8,Fclear role. It should protect and
OL,9,Fpreserve life, not take it away. The
OL,10,Fstate should never offer death as a
OL,11,Fservice."
OL,13,FShe said "the greatest risk of all is
OL,14,Fthe pressure the elderly, vulnerable,
OL,15,Fsick or disabled may place upon
OL,16,Fthemselves".
