OL,6,FThe intervention appears to be at odds
OL,7,Fwith guidance set out by Cabinet
OL,8,FSecretary Simon Case last month that
OL,9,Fministers should remain neutral on the
OL,10,Fissue and avoid taking part in public
OL,11,Fdebate.
OL,13,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer has
OL,14,Fdeclined to say whether he will back
OL,15,Fthe Bill, arguing that he does not
OL,16,Fwant to pressure MPs. Members will be
OL,17,Fgiven a free vote to act according to
OL,18,Ftheir personal beliefs, rather than in
OL,19,Fline with party policy.
