OL,6,FBut prominent figures including former
OL,7,Fprime minister Gordon Brown have
OL,8,Fvoiced opposition to the legislation.
OL,10,FMs Mahmood, Mr Streeting and Education
OL,11,FSecretary Bridget Phillipson have said
OL,12,Fthey will vote against the Bill while
OL,13,Fcare minister Stephen Kinnock said he
OL,14,Fsupports it.
OL,16,FProponents argue existing legislation
OL,17,Ffails to respect patient autonomy and
OL,18,Fdiscriminates financially between
OL,19,Fthose who can afford to travel abroad
OL,20,Fto end their lives within the law and
OL,21,Fthose who cannot.
